<br>
“Chloe,” he greeted, handing the cashier the money for both their orders. She arched an eyebrow and crossed her arms.<br>
<br>
“Are you stalking me now?” She quipped. He grinned.<br>
<br>
“Of course not,” he paused. “I have people to do that for me.” Despite herself, Chloe laughed and flashed an honest smile at Lex. “Glad you’re in a better mood today.” She rolled her eyes and grabbed her cup from the attendant. He went to hold the door open for her.<br>
<br>
“You know, that’s the second time you’ve done that.” He furrowed his brow.<br>
<br>
“Done what?”<br>
<br>
